fedeconseries 0.1.0
  • Reference
  • Articles
    • Detailed usage of library fedeconseries

US federal reserve economic data series accessing This wrapper function is to access data from https://alfred.stlouisfed.org.

Source: R/fedeconseries.R
get_fedeconseries.Rd

US federal reserve economic data series accessing This wrapper function is to access data from https://alfred.stlouisfed.org.

get_fedeconseries(s_id, s_name = NULL,
obs_start = NULL, obs_end = NULL,real_start = NULL, real_end = NULL)

Arguments

s_id

econimic variable names provided by ALFRED, unique identifier.
s_name

Output column name, default is s_id.
obs_start

Date of first observation in "yyyy-mm-dd" format. Default: Earliest observation available.
obs_end

Date of last observation in "yyyy-mm-dd" format. Default: Last observation available.
real_start

Date of first real time period in "yyyy-mm-dd" format. Default: First vintage date available.
real_end

Date of last real time period in "yyyy-mm-dd" format. Default: Last vintage date available.

Details

fromJSON return: (1) $observations(4 cols: realtime_start, realtime_end, date, value); (2)other attrs: $realtime_start, $realtime_end, $observation_start, $observation_end, $units, $output_type, $file_type, $order_by, $sort_order, $count, $offset, $limit

Examples

if (FALSE) {
    get_fedeconseries("INDPRO", "indpro")
    }

get_fedeconseries("INDPRO", "indpro", real_start = "2010-01-01", real_end = "2015-12-31")
